=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex20 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 501 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 501.0658
  harmonic_decay_rate: -14.8302
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5311
  pitch_clarity: 485.8971
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.5421
  resonance_freq: 495.2637

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 20
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 20 ---
{ // distorts and envelopes z
var z;
z = FSinOsc.ar(500);
z min: FSinOsc.ar(0.1);
}.play;
